Bundled third-party code

The license above covers Movar's own code. The shipped browser extension also
bundles third-party packages (franc and its dependency closure: trigram-utils,
n-gram, collapse-white-space — all MIT) into the background worker for on-device
language detection. Their copyright and permission notices are reproduced in
apps/extension/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md, which is generated by
scripts/gen-third-party-notices.mts and shipped inside the extension artifact
(apps/extension/.output/<target>/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md).
